---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Semantic HTML" description="ply auto-styles semantic HTML elements — nav, table, dialog, details, code, and more. Start with what HTML gives you for free.">
  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">
      Getting Started
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-balance">Semantic HTML</h1>
    <p class="lead no-orphan">
      ply automatically styles 13 semantic HTML elements — no classes
      needed. Start with native elements before reaching for custom markup.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="headings"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Text</p>
    <h2>Headings</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      All heading levels are styled with a consistent type scale, weight,
      and line-height.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding" role="presentation">
      <p class="h1 no-top-margin">Heading 1</p>
      <p class="h2">Heading 2</p>
      <p class="h3">Heading 3</p>
      <p class="h4">Heading 4</p>
      <p class="h5">Heading 5</p>
      <p class="h6">Heading 6</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="nav"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Navigation</p>
    <h2>&lt;nav&gt;</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Wrap a <code>&lt;ul&gt;</code> inside <code>&lt;nav class="navbar"&gt;</code> for a horizontal navigation
      bar. ply handles active states, hover effects, and responsive
      collapse.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <nav class="navbar">
        <ul>
          <li class="active">
            <a href="#nav">Home</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="#nav">About</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="#nav">Contact</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </div>

    <CodeBlock
      code={`<nav class="navbar">
  <ul>
    <li class="active"><a href="/">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>`}
    />
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="table"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Data</p>
    <h2>&lt;table&gt;</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Tables are styled automatically — borders, padding, header styling,
      and striped rows all come free.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Role</th>
            <th>Status</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Alice</td>
            <td>Engineer</td>
            <td>Active</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Bob</td>
            <td>Designer</td>
            <td>Active</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Charlie</td>
            <td>PM</td>
            <td>Away</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="code"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Code</p>
    <h2>&lt;code&gt; & &lt;pre&gt;</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Inline <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> gets a subtle background and
      monospace font. Block <code>&lt;pre&gt;</code> elements get padding,
      border-radius, and horizontal scroll.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <p>
        Inline: <code>const x = 42;</code>
      </p>
      <pre><code set:text={`function greet(name) {\n  return \`Hello, \${name}!\`;\n}`} /></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="kbd"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Keyboard</p>
    <h2>&lt;kbd&gt;</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Keyboard input elements get a raised, bordered appearance.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <p>
        Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>K</kbd> to open search.
      </p>
      <p>
        Use <kbd>Tab</kbd> to navigate, <kbd>Enter</kbd> to select.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="blockquote"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Quote</p>
    <h2>&lt;blockquote&gt;</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Block quotes get a left border accent and italic styling.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          Start with semantic HTML before reaching for classes. ply gives
          you a lot for free.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="mark"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Highlight</p>
    <h2>&lt;mark&gt;</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      The <code>&lt;mark&gt;</code> element highlights text with a
      theme-aware background.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <p>
        You can <mark>highlight important text</mark> with the mark element.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="details"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Disclosure</p>
    <h2>&lt;details&gt; & &lt;summary&gt;</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Native disclosure widgets with styled toggle indicators.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <details>
        <summary>Click to expand</summary>
        <p>
          This content is hidden by default and revealed when the user
          clicks the summary. No JavaScript needed.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Another expandable section</summary>
        <p>
          You can have multiple details elements. Each toggles
          independently.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="dialog"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Modal</p>
    <h2>&lt;dialog&gt;</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Native HTML dialog element with automatic backdrop, centering, and
      styling.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <button
        class="btn btn-blue"
        onclick="document.getElementById('semantic-dialog').showModal()"
      >
        Open Dialog
      </button>
      <dialog id="semantic-dialog" aria-labelledby="semantic-dialog-title">
        <h3 id="semantic-dialog-title">Native Dialog</h3>
        <p>
          This dialog is styled automatically by ply. Use <code>.showModal()</code> to open it.
        </p>
        <div class="btn-group align-right">
          <button
            class="btn btn-outline"
            onclick="document.getElementById('semantic-dialog').close()"
          >
            Close
          </button>
        </div>
      </dialog>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra border-bottom"
    id="progress"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Indicators</p>
    <h2>&lt;progress&gt; & &lt;meter&gt;</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Progress bars and meter elements are styled with theme-aware colors.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <label class="display-block bottom-margin">
        Progress (70%)
        <progress value="70" max="100"></progress>
      </label>
      <label class="display-block bottom-margin">
        Meter (low)
        <meter
          value="0.2"
          min="0"
          max="1"
          low="0.3"
          high="0.7"
          optimum="0.8"
        ></meter>
      </label>
      <label class="display-block">
        Meter (high)
        <meter
          value="0.9"
          min="0"
          max="1"
          low="0.3"
          high="0.7"
          optimum="0.8"
        ></meter>
      </label>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra" id="forms">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Input</p>
    <h2>Form Elements</h2>
    <p class="no-orphan">
      Inputs, selects, textareas, checkboxes, and radio buttons are all
      styled when wrapped in a <code>.form</code> container. Labels
      automatically stack with their inputs.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-radius padding">
      <form class="form">
        <label>
          Text input
          <input type="text" placeholder="Styled automatically" />
        </label>
        <label>
          Select
          <select>
            <option>Option one</option>
            <option>Option two</option>
          </select>
        </label>
        <label>
          <input type="checkbox" checked /> Checkbox
        </label>
      </form>
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm text-secondary no-orphan">
      See <a href="/docs/forms">Forms</a> for the full forms reference
      including sizes, validation states, and input groups.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section
    class="padding-top-extra padding-bottom-extra"
    id="next-steps"
  >
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase color-blue">Next</p>
    <h2>Next Steps</h2>
    <p class="text-secondary no-orphan">
      Customize the look with <a href="/docs/colors">Colors & Theming</a>, or explore the <a href="/docs/grid">grid system</a> for page layouts.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
